Stands for Coronavirus Disease and the 19 stands for 2019, the year it was discovered. It is called coronavirus disease because the disease (aka the symptoms) are caused by the virus SARS-COV-2.

COVID-19 is the disease caused by the virus SARS-COV-2. SARS stands for Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome (acute means short in a medical sense), COV stands for coronavirus, the type of virus, and 2 is because it is the second type of this virus identified. COVID-19...
